WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.160
Chapter 1 Smile, please.

00:04.160 --> 00:14.080
Kit Chippans sat down on the harbor wall and looked across the bay. The sun was hot,

00:14.080 --> 00:20.240
and there wasn't a cloud in the sky. But Kit wasn't happy.

00:21.200 --> 00:28.640
There aren't any tourists this morning, he thought. I'm not going to earn much money today.

00:30.160 --> 00:37.680
The weather information on the radio said rain, and tourists always listen to weather information.

00:38.960 --> 00:42.320
But it was wrong. It isn't raining.

00:42.960 --> 00:50.480
Kit looked at the old camera in his hand. It belonged to his father.

00:52.240 --> 00:55.440
Kit wanted to earn money to buy a new camera.

00:57.200 --> 01:02.000
In the school holidays, he took photographs of the visitors to his town.

01:03.200 --> 01:10.320
He loved taking photos. The tourists liked Kit. He smiled a lot,

01:11.040 --> 01:13.280
and he took good photographs of them.

01:15.440 --> 01:21.520
Kit's town was on a pretty bay. Some people there earned money from fishing,

01:22.560 --> 01:30.000
and some people worked in the small hotels beside the bay. Rich people came there on holiday.

01:31.520 --> 01:35.840
They liked to sail yachts between the small islands across the bay.

01:36.320 --> 01:42.960
Kit looked at summer cloud. It was the biggest yacht in the harbor,

01:42.960 --> 01:51.760
and it belonged to Bob Chapman. Bob's clients were always rich and famous people.

01:53.680 --> 01:58.800
Who has hired Bob Chapman's yacht today? Kit thought.

01:58.800 --> 02:07.200
Kit thought, well, I know one thing. He won't give me any information. He never does.

02:09.120 --> 02:15.440
Kit was right. Bob Chapman promised his famous clients three things.

02:16.320 --> 02:21.360
Good sailing, good food, and no paparazzi.

02:21.360 --> 02:29.600
In a house on a hill above the bay, Anna Lee was unhappy, too.

02:31.440 --> 02:40.000
What am I going to do at home, Mom? She said, I'm 15, and I haven't got a holiday job.

02:41.280 --> 02:47.760
And all my friends are away. That's not a problem, said her mother.

02:48.720 --> 02:55.520
You can clean the house for me. I don't like cleaning very much, said Anna.

02:56.800 --> 03:03.280
Can I do the cooking? The phone rang, and Anna's mother went to answer it.

03:04.720 --> 03:11.360
It was Bob Chapman. He was a friend of the family, and he wanted to speak to Anna.

03:12.240 --> 03:19.040
Hello, Anna, said Bob. What are you doing for the next three days?

03:20.480 --> 03:27.680
Erm, not much, said Anna. Why, Bob? I've got a problem.

03:29.040 --> 03:35.520
Some clients want to sail to Moon Island tomorrow. I really want to do this job,

03:36.240 --> 03:42.560
and I've promised them. But Lily is ill. She cooks and cleans for me.

03:43.760 --> 03:50.800
Can you help, Anna? You're good at cooking, aren't you? You cooked a great meal for your mother's

03:50.800 --> 03:58.160
birthday. You'll only have to cook one meal, lunch. We'll have dinner on the island.

03:59.120 --> 04:09.200
Yes, said Anna. Well, I'll have to ask Moon. But yes, I'd like to. I'm a good cook.

04:10.640 --> 04:20.240
Who are your clients? I can't tell you yet, said Bob. You know why. I promised my clients

04:20.240 --> 04:26.640
no paparazzi. Can you come today, Anna? They want to leave early in the morning.

04:28.160 --> 04:34.960
You'll have to clean the cabins and make the beds this afternoon, and do some shopping for me.

04:35.680 --> 04:44.640
Is that okay? Okay, said Anna. I'll ask Moon to drive me down to the harbor. Thank you, Bob.

04:45.600 --> 04:52.080
I'll see you later. Anna put down the phone and talked to her mother about the job.

04:52.880 --> 04:59.920
I'll work hard, she said. Maybe Bob will give me a job on his boat for the summer.

05:02.160 --> 05:06.960
It didn't rain, and some tourists came to the harbor in the afternoon.

05:08.080 --> 05:12.720
Smile, please, said Kit, and he took their photographs.

05:14.720 --> 05:19.120
From the deck of a black motorboat, a young woman watched Kit.

05:22.160 --> 05:29.360
A photographer, she thought. Perhaps he'll know about that big yacht in the harbor.

05:31.360 --> 05:36.880
A car arrived at the harbor. The woman watched a girl with short hair get out.

05:38.160 --> 05:43.440
A man met the girl, took her bag, and helped her into a small boat.

05:44.320 --> 05:52.080
He was tall with white hair, and he wore a life jacket. His face was browned from being in the sun.

05:52.960 --> 06:00.160
The girl put on a life jacket. Then the small boat made its way out to the big yacht.

06:01.760 --> 06:11.200
Tommy, the woman called, come here. A big, strong man came up onto the deck of the motorboat.

06:12.080 --> 06:15.840
He wore a large white hat and a jacket.

06:16.560 --> 06:19.600
What do you want, Jade? He asked.

06:20.640 --> 06:26.720
The woman looked at Kit, then across the water at Anna on summer cloud.

06:27.920 --> 06:33.120
What do you think? She asked, yes or no.

06:33.360 --> 06:41.040
Tommy understood. He touched his jacket, where he had a small gun.

06:42.320 --> 06:48.320
He suddenly smiled. Yes, my dear. He answered.

06:52.400 --> 06:59.440
Track three. In a house on a hill above the bay, Anna Lee was unhappy too.

07:00.400 --> 07:09.920
What am I going to do at home, Mom? She said, I'm 15, and I haven't got a holiday job.

07:11.200 --> 07:13.520
And all my friends are away.

07:14.880 --> 07:20.480
That's not a problem, said her mother. You can clean the house for me.

07:21.680 --> 07:27.920
I don't like cleaning very much, said Anna. Can I do the cooking?

07:29.600 --> 07:33.200
The phone rang, and Anna's mother went to answer it.

07:34.640 --> 07:41.280
It was Bob Chapman. He was a friend of the family, and he wanted to speak to Anna.

07:42.880 --> 07:49.040
Hello, Anna, said Bob. What are you doing for the next three days?

07:50.000 --> 07:55.120
Uh, not much, said Anna. Why Bob?

07:56.400 --> 08:02.480
I've got a problem. Some clients want to sail to Moon Island tomorrow.

08:03.440 --> 08:07.280
I really want to do this job, and I've promised them.

08:08.320 --> 08:12.480
But Lily is ill. She cooks and cleans for me.

08:13.680 --> 08:17.520
Can you help Anna? You're good at cooking, aren't you?

08:18.480 --> 08:21.280
You cooked a great meal for your mother's birthday.

08:22.320 --> 08:28.080
You'll only have to cook one meal. Lunch. We'll have dinner on the island.

08:32.240 --> 08:34.880
Chapter 2. Harbor Life

08:36.640 --> 08:38.640
Jade sat on the harbor wall.

08:39.360 --> 08:42.320
Kit saw her. Held up his camera and said,

08:43.040 --> 08:51.120
Smile, please. Jade didn't smile. No, please don't take my photo, she said.

08:52.400 --> 09:01.600
Then she stood up and put out her hand. Hello. My name is Jade, and I work for a new magazine,

09:02.560 --> 09:07.760
Harbor Life. And I'm looking for photographs of famous people.

09:08.560 --> 09:12.960
We want to write a story about famous visitors to this harbor.

09:14.160 --> 09:18.560
I've seen you take a lot of photographs. Are they good?

09:19.840 --> 09:24.480
Yes, said Kit. He smiled and shook Jade's hand.

09:25.760 --> 09:30.160
My name's Kit Jipan, and I work here in the school holidays.

09:31.280 --> 09:33.840
I want to earn money to buy a better camera.

09:34.640 --> 09:44.800
Erm, are you staying in town? No. I arrived this morning. My boat's over there, said Jade.

09:46.320 --> 09:49.440
Then she looked across the harbor at Summer Cloud.

09:51.200 --> 09:56.320
That's a beautiful yacht out there, isn't it? Who has hired it, Kit?

09:57.280 --> 10:02.240
Do you know, I'd like some photographs of its clients for my magazine,

10:03.040 --> 10:09.280
and some information about them. You know, about their life, their work.

10:10.800 --> 10:12.640
Could you do that for me?

10:14.240 --> 10:22.400
Kit stopped smiling. Oh, I'm sorry. But Bob Chapman doesn't give information about his clients.

10:23.200 --> 10:25.920
You can talk to his crew, can't you?

10:26.880 --> 10:27.600
Asked Jade.

10:28.400 --> 10:31.760
No, said Kit. I'm sorry, but I can't.

10:32.720 --> 10:37.360
Yes, you can, said Jade. I'll pay you well.

10:38.400 --> 10:40.320
Then you can buy your new camera.

10:41.600 --> 10:43.040
She smiled and waited.

10:44.240 --> 10:49.920
I do need a new camera, for Kit, and I do want to be a photographer.

10:50.800 --> 10:52.560
And this woman is nice.

10:54.400 --> 10:55.200
Why not?

10:56.000 --> 10:58.160
I'll do it, he said.

11:00.000 --> 11:04.160
Okay, you're hired, said Jade.

11:05.520 --> 11:06.960
They shook hands again.

11:07.760 --> 11:12.960
Come to my boat tonight. Let's say, at six o'clock?

11:13.760 --> 11:19.920
I can't promise to get any photos of the clients, said Kit. That's okay.

11:20.960 --> 11:25.120
Try to get some information, and we can talk about it tonight.

11:26.160 --> 11:27.840
She walked back to the motorboat.

11:28.960 --> 11:32.560
Kit looked at his watch. It was four o'clock.

11:33.760 --> 11:36.640
I've only got two hours, he thought.

11:39.520 --> 11:41.040
Anna's mother called her.

11:41.840 --> 11:44.640
I can't talk, Mum, said Anna.

11:45.440 --> 11:47.200
Yes, I've cleaned the cabins.

11:47.840 --> 11:50.960
But I've got to do some shopping for tomorrow's lunch.

11:51.440 --> 11:55.040
And, oh, I haven't made the beds yet.

11:56.080 --> 11:58.320
Sorry, Mum. I've got to go.

12:00.240 --> 12:02.880
Bob was happy with Anna's hard work.

12:03.760 --> 12:05.680
It was a good time to tell her.

12:06.640 --> 12:08.320
Anna? He called.

12:08.960 --> 12:10.320
Stop work and listen.

12:11.680 --> 12:14.160
Do you want to know the names of my clients?

12:15.040 --> 12:18.720
Yes, please, said Anna, and she sat down.

12:19.760 --> 12:21.840
Okay, said Bob.

12:22.720 --> 12:24.960
They're famous film stars.

12:25.920 --> 12:28.400
They're making a new film on Moon Island.

12:29.200 --> 12:31.920
There's a big film crew on the island already.

12:32.640 --> 12:35.920
But, Anna, you mustn't talk about it.

12:36.640 --> 12:39.360
I won't, said Anna. I promise.

12:40.320 --> 12:42.000
Tell me, please, Bob.

12:42.800 --> 12:43.600
Who are they?

12:44.800 --> 12:45.680
Bob smiled.

12:46.640 --> 12:52.240
Well, she likes diamond rings and the colour green.

12:53.200 --> 12:56.000
And he's been in two films with her,

12:56.800 --> 13:00.880
and Charles Ford and Maria Chilini.

13:01.680 --> 13:05.120
Anna got up and jumped up and down on the deck.

13:05.680 --> 13:08.480
Wow! Chas and Chilini!

13:09.200 --> 13:11.040
They're in all the magazines.

13:11.440 --> 13:13.520
I read about them every week.

13:14.000 --> 13:16.240
She always wears diamond rings,

13:16.240 --> 13:19.280
and she always has white flowers in her room.

13:19.280 --> 13:23.520
And he, white flowers, Bob said suddenly.

13:24.240 --> 13:28.480
Anna, can you go and buy some white flowers for her cabin?

13:28.560 --> 13:32.400
Okay, I'll go now, said Anna.

13:32.400 --> 13:35.280
I've got to buy the fish as well.

13:36.960 --> 13:40.080
Anna took the small boat back to the harbor wall.

13:40.080 --> 13:44.080
She went to the market, and five minutes later,

13:44.080 --> 13:49.040
she came out with her arms full of big, white flowers.

13:49.040 --> 13:52.640
She stood in the sunshine and smelled them.

13:52.640 --> 13:56.080
She was the happiest girl in the world.

13:58.560 --> 14:00.960
I can tell all my friends at school.

14:01.840 --> 14:06.080
I've met Chas and Chilini, she thought.

14:08.720 --> 14:10.560
Kit held up his camera.

14:11.120 --> 14:13.600
Smile, please, he said to Anna.

14:14.400 --> 14:18.400
Hello, I'm taking photographs for a new magazine,

14:19.040 --> 14:19.840
Harbor Life.

14:21.040 --> 14:23.680
Aren't you young to be a magazine photographer?

14:24.480 --> 14:25.200
Anna asked.

14:26.080 --> 14:28.080
I'm 16, said Kit.

14:28.880 --> 14:30.160
It's my holiday job.

14:31.040 --> 14:33.520
I want to be a photographer when I leave school,

14:34.320 --> 14:36.160
but I need a better camera for that.

14:37.360 --> 14:38.640
Are you on holiday here?

14:39.600 --> 14:42.480
No, I live here, said Anna.

14:43.200 --> 14:45.360
I'm working on that big yacht over there.

14:46.080 --> 14:49.280
Summer Cloud, it belongs to my mother's friend.

14:50.240 --> 14:54.240
Yes, Bob Chapman, I know him, said Kit.

14:55.200 --> 14:57.280
You know Bob, asked Anna.

14:58.000 --> 15:01.520
Yes, he's a good sailor, one of the best.

15:02.720 --> 15:05.040
I'm Kit, what's your name?

15:06.240 --> 15:09.600
Anna, who are the flowers for, Anna?

15:10.400 --> 15:15.520
Uh, therefore one of the cabins, Anna said carefully.

15:17.280 --> 15:20.400
Anna and Kit sat down on the harbor wall.

15:21.440 --> 15:25.120
They talked and watched the fishing boats along the harbor wall.

15:25.200 --> 15:28.240
People stopped to buy fish.

15:29.680 --> 15:30.960
And what about you, Anna?

15:31.680 --> 15:32.320
Ask it.

15:33.520 --> 15:35.680
Aren't you young to be working on a boat?

15:36.720 --> 15:40.880
Oh, it's a holiday job for me too, said Anna.

15:42.080 --> 15:44.720
But it's the best holiday job in the world,

15:45.360 --> 15:49.920
Chas, and she suddenly stopped speaking and looked down.

15:50.720 --> 15:55.040
Who, said Kit, Anna thought quickly.

15:56.080 --> 15:59.360
Chapman, Bob Chapman, she said.

16:00.160 --> 16:02.240
The yacht belongs to Bob Chapman.

16:03.200 --> 16:05.840
Yes, I know, said Kit.

16:07.120 --> 16:08.560
Anna looked at her watch.

16:09.440 --> 16:11.600
I'm sorry, Kit, I must go.

16:12.560 --> 16:16.080
I've got to take these flowers to the yacht and get some fish.

16:17.760 --> 16:19.360
She stood up and walked away.

16:20.400 --> 16:21.520
Her face was hot.

16:22.640 --> 16:25.840
Oh no, did he hear Chas's name?

16:27.760 --> 16:33.040
From the harbor wall, Kit watched Anna buy some fish from one of the fishing boats.

16:34.160 --> 16:37.840
Then, with a bag of fish and the white flowers in her arms,

16:38.480 --> 16:40.160
she got into a small boat.

16:41.520 --> 16:42.720
Kit smiled.

16:43.680 --> 16:44.800
It was easy.

16:45.760 --> 16:50.240
He always read stories about famous film stars in magazines.

16:51.120 --> 16:54.640
He wanted to take photographs for those magazines one day.

16:55.920 --> 16:57.440
He remembered one story.

16:58.240 --> 17:03.280
Chas, Ford, and Maria Chilini were going to make a new film.

17:04.320 --> 17:09.760
He couldn't remember the name of it, but there was an island in the story.

17:11.200 --> 17:13.360
Was it one of the islands across the bay?

17:15.440 --> 17:21.840
Kit watched Anna take the small boats out to Summer Cloud, with the white flowers beside her.

17:23.040 --> 17:26.880
And then he remembered another story about Maria Chilini.

17:27.920 --> 17:30.560
She loved white flowers.

17:32.560 --> 17:33.280
It's them.

17:34.320 --> 17:36.400
It's Chas and Chilini.

17:37.600 --> 17:41.200
I've got some information now, Kit thought.

17:42.160 --> 17:44.480
I can tell Jade at six o'clock.

17:48.640 --> 17:53.360
Chapter three lies and more lies.

17:55.920 --> 17:59.280
It was morning and Summer Cloud was at sea.

18:00.880 --> 18:03.440
Anna couldn't see the harbor or the town.

18:04.480 --> 18:07.680
The sun shone and the sea was calm.

18:08.560 --> 18:12.240
It's nice and quiet out here, she thought.

18:13.920 --> 18:16.000
But Bob Chapman wasn't happy.

18:17.360 --> 18:21.280
We need more wind in the sails, he said to Anna.

18:22.240 --> 18:23.840
We need to go faster.

18:25.440 --> 18:31.520
Anna looked up at the white sails, the big main sail and the sail at the front.

18:33.200 --> 18:34.720
Can't you switch the engine on?

18:35.360 --> 18:35.920
She asked.

18:36.880 --> 18:40.000
I don't want to switch it on yet, replied Bob.

18:40.800 --> 18:42.720
The engine makes a lot of noise.

18:43.760 --> 18:45.760
I don't think Chas will like that.

18:47.120 --> 18:47.920
How is he now?

18:49.120 --> 18:51.920
I'll go down and see, said Anna.

18:53.600 --> 18:58.880
In his cabin, Chas forward lay on the bed with his eyes closed.

18:59.920 --> 19:02.080
He wanted to be back on land.

19:02.080 --> 19:06.720
Anna gave him a glass of water and said,

19:07.760 --> 19:09.520
drink this, Mr. Ford.

19:10.720 --> 19:12.880
He drank it and then said,

19:14.000 --> 19:16.080
I really don't feel well, Anna.

19:17.120 --> 19:21.440
This is the first time I've sailed on a yacht and I don't like it.

19:22.880 --> 19:25.040
When will we arrive at Moon Island?

19:26.480 --> 19:29.040
At the end of the day, Anna told him,

19:30.000 --> 19:31.200
you'll feel better soon.

19:32.960 --> 19:35.200
She went back up onto the deck and thought,

19:36.160 --> 19:38.960
shall I tell all my friends at school about this?

19:40.960 --> 19:45.040
At 10 o'clock, Maria Chilini came up onto the deck.

19:46.080 --> 19:51.120
She was beautiful, just like her pictures in the magazines.

19:52.560 --> 19:57.120
Her hair was long and red and her eyes were green.

19:58.000 --> 20:00.160
Her swimsuit was green too.

20:01.200 --> 20:04.240
Her diamond rings shone in the sunshine.

20:05.440 --> 20:07.600
She smiled at Anna and said,

20:08.240 --> 20:11.440
those white flowers in my cabin are beautiful.

20:11.840 --> 20:13.280
Did you put them there?

20:14.240 --> 20:17.200
Yes, Miss Chilini, replied Anna.

20:18.160 --> 20:19.120
Thank you.

20:19.760 --> 20:21.360
And call me Maria.

20:22.720 --> 20:24.720
She sat on the deck and said,

20:25.120 --> 20:27.920
come and talk to me, Anna.

20:29.520 --> 20:31.280
Anna sat down beside her.

20:32.800 --> 20:36.080
It's nice out here, isn't it, Maria?

20:36.880 --> 20:40.880
She asked, oh, it's beautiful, said Maria.

20:41.840 --> 20:43.360
Beautiful and quiet.

20:45.440 --> 20:47.280
Do you like being famous, Maria?

20:48.240 --> 20:49.040
Yes, I do.

20:50.160 --> 20:52.640
But the paparazzi can be a big problem.

20:53.600 --> 20:57.280
They always want photos, photos, photos.

20:59.440 --> 21:03.120
When did you first want to be a film star, asked Anna?

21:04.320 --> 21:10.480
Oh, I was only a little girl, about nine or ten years old.

21:11.600 --> 21:13.600
My father wasn't happy about it.

21:14.480 --> 21:19.040
He wanted me to be a doctor, but he understands now.

21:19.040 --> 21:23.760
Anna and Maria talked for a long time.

21:24.960 --> 21:27.760
She's really nice, thought Anna.

21:29.680 --> 21:34.160
The sun was high in the sky now, and Anna stood up and said,

21:34.880 --> 21:35.920
I'm sorry, Maria.

21:36.800 --> 21:38.400
I've got to go and cook the lunch.

21:39.600 --> 21:40.560
What are you cooking?

21:41.360 --> 21:45.120
Maria asked, fish, replied Anna.

21:45.920 --> 21:48.160
Oh, I love fish.

21:49.040 --> 21:52.720
Smart Maria, and she lay back in the sunshine.

21:55.200 --> 21:56.880
Kit opened his eyes.

21:57.920 --> 21:58.640
It was dark.

21:59.840 --> 22:02.000
He could hear the sound of an engine.

22:03.200 --> 22:05.360
Then he heard the sound of seabirds.

22:06.480 --> 22:10.880
He stood up, found a light switch, and switched on the light.

22:12.400 --> 22:17.680
He was in a small cabin without a window, and it moved from side to side.

22:19.840 --> 22:22.880
I'm on a boat, and it's moving.

22:24.960 --> 22:26.160
What am I doing here?

22:27.920 --> 22:29.040
He looked at his watch.

22:30.240 --> 22:32.640
It was three o'clock in the afternoon.

22:34.640 --> 22:36.560
He tried to remember the night before.

22:38.240 --> 22:42.480
Yes, I went to the motorboat at six o'clock.

22:43.280 --> 22:48.960
I told Jade and Tommy about Chas Ford and Maria Chilini,

22:49.840 --> 22:51.120
and they were nice to me.

22:52.320 --> 22:54.160
They liked my photos of the harbor.

22:55.680 --> 22:56.560
Then what happened?

22:58.080 --> 22:59.200
I can't remember.

23:01.760 --> 23:03.920
He sat down and thought hard.

23:05.440 --> 23:07.920
Yes, that's it.

23:09.280 --> 23:12.320
I wanted to leave, and I got up.

23:12.960 --> 23:14.960
And what was it?

23:16.160 --> 23:16.800
A drink?

23:18.320 --> 23:20.240
Jade gave me a drink.

23:22.160 --> 23:23.680
It had a nasty taste.

23:25.680 --> 23:29.120
Kit switched on his mobile phone to call his father,

23:30.240 --> 23:31.760
but his phone didn't work.

23:34.000 --> 23:37.120
I trusted Jade and Tommy, he thought.

23:38.480 --> 23:40.160
But I don't really know them.

23:42.800 --> 23:47.520
Kit opened the door of the cabin and ran angrily up the stairs.

23:48.960 --> 23:51.200
He was on the deck of the black motorboat.

23:52.160 --> 23:54.400
The sun shone in a blue sky.

23:55.680 --> 23:58.800
Tommy was at the steering wheel with Jade beside him.

23:59.920 --> 24:05.680
Kit couldn't see any land, but he could see the sails of summer cloud

24:05.680 --> 24:07.120
a long way in front of them.

24:08.400 --> 24:10.640
Now he was angry and worried.

24:11.440 --> 24:13.600
Why did I trust them?

24:14.400 --> 24:14.960
He thought.

24:17.280 --> 24:20.480
Tommy, Jade, he shouted.

24:21.520 --> 24:22.320
What's happening?

24:23.440 --> 24:24.560
Where are we going?

24:25.760 --> 24:29.040
Jade turned and said, hello, Kit.

24:30.160 --> 24:31.280
Do you want some lunch?

24:32.400 --> 24:34.800
No thanks, replied Kit.

24:35.920 --> 24:37.920
Why am I here on your motorboat?

24:38.800 --> 24:40.880
My father will be very worried.

24:41.840 --> 24:42.880
Jade smiled.

24:43.680 --> 24:44.720
You went to sleep.

24:45.760 --> 24:49.600
I tried to stop you, but you were very tired.

24:51.040 --> 24:52.560
You can call your father now.

24:53.520 --> 24:55.120
Tell him about your new job.

24:56.400 --> 24:59.680
My mobile doesn't work here, said Kit.

25:00.560 --> 25:01.440
I'm what job?

25:02.400 --> 25:05.360
I've already told you about Chas and Chilini.

25:06.240 --> 25:08.880
Why are we following Bob Chapman's yacht?

25:10.560 --> 25:14.720
Jade held the steering wheel and Tommy came to talk to Kit.

25:16.320 --> 25:19.600
You're a good photographer, Kit, he said.

25:20.640 --> 25:24.560
We just want you to take some photographs of Maria and Chas

25:25.600 --> 25:26.560
for the magazine.

25:28.000 --> 25:32.480
No, don't be silly, Kit, said Tommy.

25:33.440 --> 25:34.560
Think about the money.

25:35.840 --> 25:38.320
Don't you want to buy your new camera?

25:39.680 --> 25:41.920
Kit looked at Jade and Tommy.

25:42.880 --> 25:45.280
Their faces looked hard in the sunlight.

25:46.480 --> 25:48.480
He really didn't trust them now.

25:49.840 --> 25:54.000
He remembered Anna's happy face and remembered her words.

25:55.200 --> 25:58.080
It's the best holiday job in the world.

26:00.080 --> 26:03.680
Bob Chapman doesn't like paparazzi, said Kit.

26:04.480 --> 26:06.480
He'll just sail away from you.

26:07.600 --> 26:10.000
No, he won't, said Tommy.

26:10.960 --> 26:12.080
He won't have time.

26:14.160 --> 26:19.200
Well, I won't take any photographs for you, Kit told them.

26:20.480 --> 26:27.440
Take me back to the harbor now, but Tommy and Jade just smiled.

26:28.160 --> 26:29.520
Track four.

26:30.720 --> 26:35.360
At 10 o'clock, Maria Chilini came up onto the deck.

26:36.240 --> 26:41.040
She was beautiful, just like her pictures in the magazines.

26:42.240 --> 26:47.520
Her hair was long and red and her eyes were green.

26:48.480 --> 26:50.800
Her swimsuit was green too.

26:52.000 --> 26:54.800
Her diamond rings shone in the sun.

26:55.120 --> 26:58.000
Her diamond rings shone in the sunshine.

26:59.600 --> 27:01.200
She smiled at Anna and said,

27:02.320 --> 27:05.200
Those white flowers in my cabin are beautiful.

27:06.000 --> 27:07.120
Did you put them there?

27:08.320 --> 27:10.880
Yes, Miss Chilini, replied Anna.

27:12.160 --> 27:12.720
Thank you.

27:13.680 --> 27:15.200
And call me Maria.

27:16.800 --> 27:18.720
She sat on the deck and said,

27:19.920 --> 27:21.120
Come and talk to me, Anna.

27:22.720 --> 27:24.480
Anna sat down beside her.

27:25.680 --> 27:29.200
It's nice out here, isn't it, Maria?

27:30.000 --> 27:34.080
She asked, Oh, it's beautiful, said Maria.

27:34.960 --> 27:36.560
Beautiful and quiet.

27:38.560 --> 27:40.480
Do you like being famous, Maria?

27:41.360 --> 27:42.160
Yes, I do.

27:43.280 --> 27:45.840
But the paparazzi can be a big problem.

27:46.720 --> 27:50.480
They always want photos, photos, photos.

27:51.120 --> 27:54.080
When did you first want to be a film star?

27:54.880 --> 27:55.680
Ask Anna.

27:56.640 --> 28:02.640
Oh, I was only a little girl, about nine or ten years old.

28:03.680 --> 28:05.680
My father wasn't happy about it.

28:06.480 --> 28:11.120
He wanted me to be a doctor, but he understands now.

28:14.720 --> 28:16.720
Chapter 4

28:17.920 --> 28:19.920
Paparazzi

28:21.440 --> 28:26.320
At four o'clock in the afternoon, Chaz came onto the deck with Maria.

28:27.600 --> 28:29.760
Maria wore a white dress.

28:31.040 --> 28:33.840
Chaz wore a gray shirt and trousers.

28:34.960 --> 28:36.800
His face was very white.

28:38.320 --> 28:42.480
Bob was standing by his radio and they went to talk to him.

28:44.400 --> 28:47.200
I like the sea, said Maria.

28:48.160 --> 28:50.000
There are no paparazzi here.

28:51.440 --> 28:54.240
Not on my yacht, replied Bob.

28:55.360 --> 28:59.440
Then he said to Chaz, How are you now, Mr. Ford?

29:00.800 --> 29:03.200
Better, thanks, said Chaz.

29:04.320 --> 29:05.360
But he was worried.

29:06.640 --> 29:08.480
The wind was stronger now.

29:09.520 --> 29:11.600
There were black clouds in the sky.

29:13.280 --> 29:15.120
Is there going to be a storm?

29:15.920 --> 29:16.480
He asked.

29:17.360 --> 29:19.600
I don't know, said Bob.

29:20.560 --> 29:23.760
I've switched on my radio for more weather information.

29:25.520 --> 29:26.880
When will we be there?

29:27.600 --> 29:28.320
Asked Chaz.

29:29.280 --> 29:31.680
Soon, Mr. Ford replied Bob.

29:32.480 --> 29:36.320
Look, you can see some of the mountains on Moon Island,

29:37.920 --> 29:39.280
under those clouds.

29:40.560 --> 29:42.240
But what about the storm?

29:43.040 --> 29:43.680
Chaz asked.

29:44.560 --> 29:47.040
Don't worry, Mr. Ford, said Bob.

29:47.920 --> 29:49.040
You're safe with me.

29:50.000 --> 29:52.480
I've been a sailor for 40 years.

29:53.520 --> 29:55.200
We can take down the sails.

29:56.160 --> 29:57.840
My yacht has a big engine.

30:00.320 --> 30:05.840
Jade drove the motorboat quickly and soon it was close to summer cloud.

30:07.040 --> 30:09.360
Kit could see the people on the deck.

30:10.320 --> 30:12.000
He forgot Tommy and Jade.

30:12.720 --> 30:15.040
He saw only Maria Chilini.

30:16.000 --> 30:19.360
Her white dress shone in the afternoon light.

30:21.120 --> 30:23.280
Get your camera out, Kit.

30:24.160 --> 30:28.000
I need those photographs, he heard Tommy say.

30:28.960 --> 30:30.480
No, said Kit.

30:31.280 --> 30:36.240
He turned around to speak to Tommy and his eyes opened wide.

30:37.520 --> 30:39.360
Tommy had a gun.

30:40.720 --> 30:42.640
He touched Kit's arm with it.

30:43.600 --> 30:44.240
Now!

30:45.200 --> 30:46.240
Tommy shouted.

30:47.600 --> 30:51.520
Kit took his camera out of his jacket and held it up.

30:54.160 --> 30:58.800
Anna heard the noise of an engine and turned and saw the motorboat.

30:59.760 --> 31:01.280
It was nearly beside them.

31:02.960 --> 31:04.400
Where did that come from?

31:05.280 --> 31:05.920
She thought.

31:06.880 --> 31:07.920
She looked at it again.

31:09.280 --> 31:11.760
That's the black motorboat from the harbor.

31:13.600 --> 31:19.280
Then she saw the young man at the rail of the motorboat with a camera in his hands.

31:20.480 --> 31:21.360
It was Kit.

31:22.640 --> 31:23.760
Anna was worried.

31:24.800 --> 31:25.520
Oh no!

31:26.720 --> 31:29.040
Did he hear Chaz's name yesterday?

31:30.240 --> 31:34.000
Did he talk to me to get information about Bob's clients?

31:35.440 --> 31:37.600
No, he was nice.

31:38.640 --> 31:39.600
I liked him.

31:40.720 --> 31:42.160
But what's he doing here?

31:43.200 --> 31:48.720
Bob saw the motorboat too and he put down the radio.

31:50.640 --> 31:53.040
Paparazzi, he shouted.

31:53.920 --> 31:55.520
And they're coming towards us.

31:56.720 --> 31:58.720
I can't turn a yacht around.

31:59.680 --> 32:00.720
There isn't time.

32:02.000 --> 32:04.560
Paparazzi, cried Maria.

32:05.280 --> 32:07.200
You promised us, Mr Chapman.

32:08.000 --> 32:09.280
No, Paparazzi.

32:10.480 --> 32:12.080
I'm sorry, Miss Chilini.

32:12.800 --> 32:13.360
Said Bob.

32:14.240 --> 32:15.360
There's been a problem.

32:16.960 --> 32:18.320
Get us away from them!

32:19.200 --> 32:21.040
Chaz said angrily to Bob.

32:21.760 --> 32:25.440
And he and Maria went quickly down to their cabins.

32:27.840 --> 32:28.560
Anna said,

32:29.760 --> 32:30.960
I'm the problem Bob.

32:32.000 --> 32:33.200
That photographer.

32:34.400 --> 32:34.880
He said,

32:36.640 --> 32:37.200
I thought,

32:38.240 --> 32:38.720
Anna,

32:39.600 --> 32:40.640
isn't that Kit?

32:41.520 --> 32:43.680
The young photographer from the harbour.

32:44.480 --> 32:45.120
Asked Bob.

32:46.560 --> 32:48.800
Did you talk to him yesterday?

32:49.920 --> 32:53.600
Well, I didn't say a lot.

32:54.320 --> 32:54.960
Said Anna.

32:55.680 --> 32:55.840
But,

32:57.840 --> 32:58.720
I'm sorry Bob.

32:59.840 --> 33:01.440
I did say Chaz's name.

33:02.560 --> 33:03.520
Oh, Anna!

33:04.240 --> 33:05.120
You promised!

33:06.080 --> 33:06.640
Said Bob.

33:07.600 --> 33:08.480
He was angry.

33:09.440 --> 33:11.200
He looked again at the motorboat.

33:12.400 --> 33:14.800
But I don't understand this.

33:15.840 --> 33:18.800
Maria and Chaz aren't on deck now.

33:19.840 --> 33:22.080
Why is the boat coming towards us?

33:23.120 --> 33:24.160
What do they want?

33:25.600 --> 33:27.520
Why hasn't it turned away?

33:29.120 --> 33:32.000
Anna went to the rail of the yacht and shouted,

33:32.880 --> 33:33.440
Go away!

33:34.400 --> 33:35.040
Go away!

33:36.400 --> 33:37.600
Kit couldn't hear her.

33:38.320 --> 33:39.120
She knew that.

33:39.840 --> 33:41.040
But she was angry.

33:41.920 --> 33:43.680
And she wanted to shout at him.

33:47.760 --> 33:48.640
Chapter 5.

33:50.000 --> 33:50.640
Pirates

33:52.640 --> 33:55.360
Kit could see Anna's angry face.

33:56.160 --> 33:57.200
And he was sorry.

33:58.160 --> 33:59.520
But he was worried too.

34:01.040 --> 34:03.840
We're going to hit the yacht, he thought.

34:03.840 --> 34:09.200
Kit could nearly touch the rail of Summer Cloud.

34:10.160 --> 34:12.800
He could see Bob Chapman shouting too.

34:14.960 --> 34:15.600
Turn back.

34:16.400 --> 34:18.160
Kit shouted to Tommy and Jade.

34:18.960 --> 34:20.000
This is dangerous.

34:20.880 --> 34:22.800
I can't take any photos now.

34:23.840 --> 34:25.680
Chaz and Chilini have seen us.

34:26.240 --> 34:27.760
And they've gone to their cabins.

34:28.880 --> 34:31.760
We didn't come here for photographs.

34:32.320 --> 34:33.520
Mr. Chaipan.

34:34.480 --> 34:36.320
Tommy said in a nasty voice.

34:37.520 --> 34:38.560
Thanks for your help.

34:39.840 --> 34:41.600
He pointed his gun at Kit.

34:42.480 --> 34:44.400
Now you're going to stay here.

34:45.520 --> 34:50.000
Jade and I have got another little job to do.

34:52.160 --> 34:54.400
Tommy went to the rail of the motorboat.

34:55.120 --> 34:58.320
He held a rope with a big hook at the end of it.

34:58.960 --> 35:02.080
He threw it over the rail of Summer Cloud.

35:03.040 --> 35:05.840
Then he tied the rope to the rail of the motorboat.

35:07.360 --> 35:11.680
Jade switched off the engine and left the steering wheel.

35:13.040 --> 35:14.400
She had a gun too.

35:15.680 --> 35:17.760
She and Tommy both waited.

35:19.200 --> 35:22.640
The deck of the yacht leaned down towards them.

35:23.840 --> 35:25.360
And they jumped onto it.

35:26.160 --> 35:28.960
Now Kit understood it all.

35:29.840 --> 35:32.960
There's no magazine, he thought.

35:33.680 --> 35:35.600
These people are pirates.

35:36.640 --> 35:39.680
They've come to Rob, Chaz and Chilini.

35:40.720 --> 35:42.160
And I've helped them.

35:44.000 --> 35:48.080
He watched the big yacht move up and down beside the motorboat

35:48.080 --> 35:51.200
and thought, what can I do?

35:51.280 --> 35:52.080
What can I do?

35:54.800 --> 35:58.160
On Summer Cloud, it all happened quickly.

35:59.280 --> 36:02.000
Bob ran to the radio to call for help.

36:02.800 --> 36:03.840
Tommy followed him.

36:04.960 --> 36:07.120
Jade pointed her gun at Anna.

36:08.480 --> 36:11.120
They're pirates, Anna thought.

36:12.320 --> 36:16.800
Tommy raised his gun and Anna screamed, look out Bob!

36:17.440 --> 36:21.360
But Tommy hit the back of Bob's head with his gun.

36:22.080 --> 36:24.240
And Bob fell onto the deck.

36:25.360 --> 36:30.080
Then Tommy hit the radio again and again with the gun

36:30.080 --> 36:31.360
and broke the radio.

36:32.400 --> 36:34.880
And then he took the key from the engine

36:35.600 --> 36:39.360
and threw it over the rail and into the sea.

36:41.040 --> 36:43.840
Jade's gun was cold on Anna's arm.

36:44.080 --> 36:50.080
Now, go and bring your film stars up here.

36:51.200 --> 36:53.040
She said in a quiet voice,

36:53.920 --> 36:56.640
and don't tell them why or.

36:57.920 --> 37:00.560
She pointed her gun at Bob on the deck.

37:02.320 --> 37:04.320
Anna went to Maria's cabin.

37:05.520 --> 37:07.280
She tried to smile and said,

37:07.280 --> 37:13.600
uh, hi Maria, come up on deck again.

37:14.880 --> 37:20.320
The sky is beautiful and you can really see Moon Island now.

37:21.520 --> 37:23.200
But what about the paparazzi?

37:24.000 --> 37:26.320
Asked Maria, where are they?

37:27.760 --> 37:30.960
I've got to tell her a lie, daughter.

37:32.000 --> 37:34.720
I don't want those pirates to hurt Bob again.

37:35.360 --> 37:38.240
She said, oh, they've gone.

37:39.360 --> 37:41.840
Then she went to Chaz's cabin door and called,

37:42.800 --> 37:44.960
Mr. Ford, we're nearly there.

37:46.000 --> 37:46.880
Come up on deck.

37:48.160 --> 37:49.680
Chaz opened his door.

37:50.880 --> 37:52.560
I don't feel well again.

37:53.360 --> 37:55.920
He said, then you need some air,

37:56.640 --> 37:59.840
replied Anna, and she tried to smile again.

38:02.080 --> 38:04.160
Maria and Chaz weren't happy.

38:05.040 --> 38:06.800
But they followed her up to the deck.

38:08.000 --> 38:11.280
Then at the top of the stairs, Maria screamed.

38:12.320 --> 38:15.360
Tommy pointed his gun at them and shouted,

38:16.160 --> 38:17.200
get out here.

38:18.640 --> 38:22.240
Chaz, Maria and Anna went out onto the deck.

38:23.200 --> 38:24.480
Anna looked for Bob.

38:25.200 --> 38:28.960
He was lying beside the rail now with a rope around him

38:29.840 --> 38:31.360
and his eyes were closed.

38:32.560 --> 38:33.920
This can't be happening.

38:34.720 --> 38:38.160
Anna thought, it's like being in a film.

38:40.160 --> 38:41.520
Why have you come to Robis?

38:42.320 --> 38:43.360
She asked the pirates.

38:44.320 --> 38:48.480
Tommy smiled and touched the diamond rings on Maria's hands.

38:49.760 --> 38:53.440
Small is beautiful, he said.

38:54.640 --> 38:56.480
Then he touched Jade's hand.

38:57.520 --> 38:58.880
Well, damn my dear.

38:59.920 --> 39:01.840
But Jade moved away from him.

39:02.720 --> 39:06.240
Oh, why did I speak to that boy yesterday?

39:06.960 --> 39:07.680
Anna thought.

39:08.720 --> 39:09.520
Where is he?

39:10.800 --> 39:12.240
Is he a pirate too?

39:16.400 --> 39:17.200
Track five.

39:19.040 --> 39:22.400
Kit could nearly touch the rail of Summer Cloud.

39:23.360 --> 39:26.080
He could see Bob Chapman shouting too.

39:26.240 --> 39:31.440
Turn back, Kit shouted to Tommy and Jade.

39:32.240 --> 39:33.280
This is dangerous.

39:34.160 --> 39:36.080
I can't take any photos now.

39:37.040 --> 39:41.040
Chaz and Chilini have seen us and they've gone to their cabins.

39:42.160 --> 39:46.720
We didn't come here for photographs, Mr. Chippan.

39:47.760 --> 39:49.520
Tommy said in a nasty voice.

39:50.720 --> 39:51.760
Thanks for your help.

39:53.120 --> 39:54.800
He pointed his gun at Kit.

39:55.760 --> 39:57.680
Now you're going to stay here.

39:58.800 --> 40:03.280
Jade and I have got another little job to do.

40:05.440 --> 40:07.680
Tommy went to the rail of the motorboat.

40:08.400 --> 40:11.600
He held a rope with a big hook at the end of it.

40:12.720 --> 40:15.360
He threw it over the rail of Summer Cloud.

40:16.320 --> 40:19.120
Then he tied the rope to the rail of the motorboat.

40:19.120 --> 40:25.040
Jade switched off the engine and left the steering wheel.

40:26.400 --> 40:27.680
She had a gun too.

40:29.040 --> 40:31.120
She and Tommy both waited.

40:32.560 --> 40:38.720
The deck of the yacht leaned down towards them and they jumped onto it.

40:40.400 --> 40:42.640
Now Kit understood it all.

40:44.000 --> 40:46.880
There's no magazine, he thought.

40:47.840 --> 40:49.440
These people are pirates.

40:50.560 --> 40:56.000
They've come to Rob, Chaz and Chilini and I've helped them.

41:00.000 --> 41:02.800
Chapter 6 In the Water

41:04.640 --> 41:09.280
The pirates tied Maria and Chaz to the rail of the yacht beside Bob.

41:11.280 --> 41:16.080
Tommy pulled Maria's diamond rings from her hands one by one.

41:17.440 --> 41:22.000
Then he went down to the cabins and came back with watches and money.

41:23.600 --> 41:25.840
Jade put all the things into a bag.

41:27.120 --> 41:32.960
Then both of the pirates went to the rail of the yacht and waited to jump onto the motorboat.

41:34.800 --> 41:39.520
But Tommy saw a flash of light from behind the sail at the front.

41:40.480 --> 41:42.800
He pointed his gun at it and shouted,

41:43.440 --> 41:46.640
Hey, come out, now.

41:48.000 --> 41:50.560
Kit came out from behind the sail.

41:51.840 --> 41:54.480
Get him Tommy, shouted Jade.

41:55.440 --> 41:59.760
Kit shouted, yes, come and get me Tommy.

42:01.200 --> 42:05.440
Tommy moved quickly towards Kit and tried to take his arm.

42:06.400 --> 42:10.480
Kit tried to get away, but Tommy got him.

42:12.080 --> 42:17.680
The yacht moved from side to side in the wind and the deck leaned down.

42:18.640 --> 42:20.000
It was difficult to stand.

42:21.440 --> 42:23.280
The two of them nearly fell over.

42:24.240 --> 42:27.920
Tommy tried to hold onto the rail and to Kit too.

42:29.040 --> 42:31.680
And he dropped his gun onto the deck.

42:32.560 --> 42:36.400
And then both of them fell into the sea.

42:37.440 --> 42:43.920
Tommy shouted, help, help, I can't swim.

42:45.360 --> 42:48.240
Anna ran to the rail and pointed at the water.

42:49.520 --> 42:52.800
We've got to help them, she shouted to Jade.

42:54.240 --> 42:57.600
But Jade jumped across to the motorboat and shouted,

42:58.400 --> 42:59.920
it's not my problem.

43:01.440 --> 43:04.400
Come back, you can't leave us here.

43:05.120 --> 43:09.520
Anna shouted, we can't call for help on the radio.

43:11.200 --> 43:15.200
Jade untied the motorboat and switched on the engine.

43:16.400 --> 43:20.000
And the motorboat moved quickly away from summer cloud.

43:22.720 --> 43:26.480
Anna looked at the worried faces of Chas and Maria.

43:27.680 --> 43:30.880
This isn't real, she thought.

43:33.040 --> 43:38.000
Then Bob shouted, Anna, get the life jackets.

43:39.200 --> 43:40.800
Anna heard Bob's voice.

43:41.600 --> 43:42.560
He was okay.

43:43.760 --> 43:48.400
He shouted again, the life jackets quickly.

43:49.440 --> 43:51.200
And now Anna moved.

43:52.800 --> 43:56.480
She took two life jackets and threw them into the sea.

43:57.760 --> 44:02.960
She couldn't see Kit or the pirate now, but she could hear their shouts.

44:03.920 --> 44:08.400
In the strong wind, summer cloud moved quickly away from them.

44:10.080 --> 44:12.880
Kit saw Tommy near him in the water.

44:13.680 --> 44:19.520
Tommy shouted, help, help, and tried to stay up.

44:20.800 --> 44:24.640
Kit swam to him and held his head out of the water.

44:25.600 --> 44:28.160
Then he saw the two life jackets.

44:29.200 --> 44:34.240
Come on, he shouted, we've got to get those life jackets.

44:35.920 --> 44:42.560
But Tommy just shouted, help, help, I can't swim.

44:44.720 --> 44:48.480
Kit held Tommy and swam to the life jackets.

44:49.280 --> 44:50.240
It was difficult.

44:51.120 --> 44:55.360
Tommy was heavy in the water, and the waves were big.

44:56.320 --> 45:00.480
He lifted Tommy's arms and put them into a life jacket.

45:02.160 --> 45:03.760
Kit was afraid.

45:04.800 --> 45:10.480
The sky was dark with rain clouds now, and he couldn't see summer cloud.

45:12.000 --> 45:13.040
Where is the yacht?

45:13.680 --> 45:14.240
He thought.

45:15.360 --> 45:17.120
They must come back for us.

45:18.000 --> 45:19.200
Untie me, Anna.

45:19.680 --> 45:24.480
Bob shouted, we've got to turn the yacht around and go back for them.

45:25.440 --> 45:28.000
But you'll have to help me take down the main sail.

45:29.040 --> 45:30.240
My head hurts.

45:30.960 --> 45:32.480
I don't feel well.

45:33.520 --> 45:37.440
Anna took the rope off Bob, but he couldn't stand up.

45:38.400 --> 45:40.800
Then she untied Chaz and Maria too.

45:42.320 --> 45:45.520
With their help, Anna took down the main sail.

45:48.080 --> 45:50.000
The yacht sailed more slowly.

45:52.000 --> 45:53.760
Bob's face was very white.

45:54.960 --> 45:58.400
You'll have to turn the tiller, Anna, he said.

45:59.680 --> 46:04.240
Turn it to the left, then to the right, slowly.

46:05.840 --> 46:08.720
Anna listened to Bob and moved the tiller.

46:10.400 --> 46:13.360
She was afraid, and her hand shook.

46:13.440 --> 46:20.480
The yacht leaned in the water, and slowly summer cloud turned around.

46:21.920 --> 46:25.840
It sailed into the wind now, and went more slowly.

46:27.600 --> 46:30.000
They all looked for the two people in the water.

46:31.520 --> 46:32.320
Can you see them?

46:32.960 --> 46:33.600
Called Anna.

46:34.800 --> 46:37.520
Then Maria shouted, there they are.

46:38.320 --> 46:43.920
Chaz, Maria and Anna pulled Tommy up the rope ladder onto the deck.

46:44.960 --> 46:46.000
It was slow work.

46:47.360 --> 46:51.680
Tommy was very heavy, and his clothes were full of water.

46:53.120 --> 46:55.280
Then they helped Kit onto the yacht.

46:56.880 --> 46:59.120
Kit stood in front of Chaz and Maria.

47:00.400 --> 47:03.360
I'm sorry about the photographs, he said.

47:04.400 --> 47:06.720
I'm sorry, I told the pirates about you.

47:07.840 --> 47:12.160
His body shook, he was cold, and afraid.

47:14.000 --> 47:19.600
Suddenly Bob shouted, hey, watch him, and pointed at Tommy.

47:20.720 --> 47:25.200
Tommy moved towards his gun on the deck, but Maria was quicker.

47:25.840 --> 47:30.640
She ran and got the gun, get back, she said to Tommy.

47:32.080 --> 47:36.400
Sit next to the rail, you two, Chaz said to Tommy and Kit.

47:37.600 --> 47:43.040
Without his gun, Tommy was afraid, and he sat down on the deck.

47:44.480 --> 47:47.280
Chaz tied Tommy and Kit to the rail.

47:48.720 --> 47:53.840
Then Maria said, I don't like guns, they're dangerous.

47:54.960 --> 48:00.560
They only belong in films, and she threw Tommy's gun into the sea.

48:00.560 --> 48:07.760
Now let's switch on the engine and get to Moon Island, said Bob.

48:09.040 --> 48:10.560
He looked at the dark clouds.

48:11.440 --> 48:15.040
We'll have to be quick, there's a big storm on the way.

48:16.160 --> 48:20.160
We can't Bob, said Anna, she pointed to Tommy.

48:20.800 --> 48:25.520
He threw the key into the sea, and he broke your radio.

48:27.600 --> 48:29.440
Bob was really worried now.

48:30.560 --> 48:33.680
Then we'll have to raise the main sail again, he said.

48:34.880 --> 48:40.720
But it's dangerous, in a storm, it could pull us into the water.

48:44.880 --> 48:48.000
Chapter 7 Lost at Sea

48:50.400 --> 48:56.960
Summer clouds sailed into the storm. The sky got darker, and it rained heavily.

48:57.920 --> 49:02.720
The sails were full of wind, and the yacht leaned towards the sea.

49:04.080 --> 49:05.760
Water came onto the deck.

49:07.520 --> 49:13.600
We're safe from the pirates, thought Anna, but we're not safe from the storm.

49:15.120 --> 49:16.960
Are we going to get to Moon Island?

49:18.880 --> 49:24.880
The wind is dangerous, Anna. We'll have to take the main sail down again, said Bob.

49:25.840 --> 49:28.480
I'm sorry, I can't do it.

49:29.280 --> 49:31.200
I'll help, said Kit.

49:31.920 --> 49:34.560
We can't trust you, shouted Anna.

49:35.200 --> 49:38.720
You've already told me lies about that new magazine.

49:39.760 --> 49:43.120
So, Kit, when can I read Harbor Life?

49:44.240 --> 49:46.560
I'm sorry, Anna, said Kit.

49:47.440 --> 49:51.040
I'm not a pirate, but I am a photographer.

49:52.240 --> 49:54.000
I only met this man yesterday.

49:55.040 --> 50:00.480
And Jade, that other pirate, she came to talk to me in the harbor.

50:01.920 --> 50:02.720
She tricked me.

50:04.400 --> 50:10.560
Yesterday, then I had the best holiday job in the world, thought Anna.

50:11.840 --> 50:14.800
Now we're all going to die out here in the storm.

50:15.600 --> 50:18.960
You tricked me, she said angrily to Kit.

50:20.560 --> 50:24.720
Maria went across the deck to Kit, and untied the rope.

50:24.960 --> 50:26.320
From his hands and feet.

50:27.680 --> 50:31.680
Anna, we need Kit's help now, she said.

50:32.640 --> 50:34.000
We've got to trust him.

50:35.280 --> 50:37.760
Thank you, Miss Chilini, said Kit.

50:38.720 --> 50:39.920
You can trust me.

50:41.120 --> 50:42.960
Let's get to work, okay?

50:44.160 --> 50:47.600
Now, let's pull hard on the main sail rope.

50:48.880 --> 50:50.400
The main sail didn't move.

50:51.600 --> 50:53.760
Pull again, shouted Bob.

50:54.640 --> 50:55.600
They pulled again.

50:56.560 --> 50:58.880
The wind was strong against their faces.

51:00.240 --> 51:04.000
The heavy sail moved suddenly, and it hit Maria.

51:05.040 --> 51:09.120
She nearly fell into the sea, but she held onto the rail.

51:10.560 --> 51:12.000
They pulled the sail down.

51:13.280 --> 51:15.360
Well done, said Bob.

51:16.320 --> 51:19.600
Then he stood up slowly, and leaned on Anna.

51:19.840 --> 51:23.040
Be careful, Bob, she said.

51:23.040 --> 51:27.120
I'm all right, Anna, he said.

51:28.400 --> 51:34.080
He looked at Tommy angrily, but I've never had pirates on my yacht,

51:34.800 --> 51:36.000
and I don't like it.

51:37.520 --> 51:39.600
Then Bob looked at Kit and said,

51:40.560 --> 51:42.240
you've been a stupid young man.

51:43.280 --> 51:45.040
What's your father going to say?

51:46.080 --> 51:49.040
They tricked me, Mr. Chapman, said Kit.

51:49.840 --> 51:55.280
They asked me to take photos of your clients, and then he stopped and said,

51:56.480 --> 51:59.040
my camera, I need to get it.

52:00.240 --> 52:02.000
I tied it to the rail up there.

52:03.440 --> 52:05.040
He went and got his camera.

52:05.760 --> 52:08.560
He looked at it and said, it's okay.

52:09.680 --> 52:12.880
Put that camera away, said Bob.

52:13.840 --> 52:15.200
Chaz was angry.

52:16.160 --> 52:20.800
Don't you understand, we don't want you to take photos.

52:21.840 --> 52:25.520
No, I'm not going to, replied Kit.

52:26.480 --> 52:31.200
He held up the camera, but I took photos of Tommy and Jade.

52:32.320 --> 52:35.200
I've got photos of them on summer cloud.

52:36.400 --> 52:40.160
Tommy looked at Kit angrily, but didn't speak.

52:41.520 --> 52:44.240
Well, let's forget that for now.

52:45.200 --> 52:48.480
Said Bob, I'm going to send up a flare.

52:49.760 --> 52:50.480
I'm worried.

52:51.920 --> 52:54.400
I don't like being out in this bad weather.

52:55.520 --> 53:00.720
There isn't a rescue helicopter on Moon Island, but they've got a lifeboat.

53:03.440 --> 53:05.840
Bob sent a flare up into the sky.

53:06.880 --> 53:09.760
It flashed red and yellow through the dark clouds.

53:10.880 --> 53:12.240
Then he sent another one.

53:13.040 --> 53:17.120
Please let the lifeboat come, thought Anna.

53:18.800 --> 53:21.920
There are only three flares, said Bob.

53:22.960 --> 53:23.920
We'll have to wait.

53:26.000 --> 53:27.440
The storm got worse.

53:28.400 --> 53:30.240
They couldn't see any land.

53:31.840 --> 53:35.680
Through the night they sat and watched for the lights of the lifeboat.

53:37.280 --> 53:41.440
It stopped raining, but it was very dark and cloudy.

53:43.200 --> 53:47.200
Bob sent up the third flare at about five o'clock in the morning.

53:48.960 --> 53:52.400
Half an hour later, they saw the lights of a boat.

53:53.440 --> 53:54.080
Over here!

53:55.040 --> 53:56.080
We're over here!

53:56.960 --> 53:57.680
They shouted.

53:59.200 --> 54:02.320
A lifeboat came and stopped beside summer cloud.

54:03.360 --> 54:05.200
One of the crew came onto the deck.

54:06.560 --> 54:09.520
We've come from Moon Island, he said.

54:10.400 --> 54:11.920
Are you Bob Chapman?

54:13.040 --> 54:14.800
Yes, Bob said.

54:15.680 --> 54:18.240
We sailed from the mainland yesterday morning.

54:19.680 --> 54:21.120
We've been lost for hours.

54:22.240 --> 54:24.160
It's been a long, dark night.

54:25.600 --> 54:28.800
We didn't see your flare, the man said.

54:29.840 --> 54:31.440
The storm was very bad.

54:32.400 --> 54:35.200
One of the film crew on the island couldn't sleep,

54:35.760 --> 54:38.800
so he got up early to take photographs of the storm.

54:39.840 --> 54:42.240
He saw the flare and he called us.

54:43.520 --> 54:45.200
But I don't understand.

54:46.240 --> 54:47.680
Why didn't you call us?

54:48.640 --> 54:50.960
And why didn't you switch on your engine?

54:52.560 --> 54:54.720
Bob Chapman looked down at Tommy.

54:56.080 --> 54:58.480
Ask him, he said.

55:02.640 --> 55:03.360
Track six.

55:05.280 --> 55:09.360
Maria went across the deck to kit and untied the rope.

55:09.600 --> 55:10.960
From his hands and feet.

55:12.320 --> 55:16.400
Anna, we need kits help now, she said.

55:17.280 --> 55:18.640
We've got to trust him.

55:19.920 --> 55:22.400
Thank you, Miss Chilini, said kit.

55:23.360 --> 55:24.560
You can trust me.

55:25.840 --> 55:27.600
Let's get to work, okay?

55:28.800 --> 55:32.320
Now, let's pull hard on the main sail rope.

55:33.520 --> 55:35.120
The main sail didn't move.

55:36.240 --> 55:36.960
Pull again!

55:37.680 --> 55:38.480
Shotted Bob.

55:39.360 --> 55:40.320
They pulled again.

55:41.280 --> 55:43.600
The wind was strong against their faces.

55:44.960 --> 55:48.720
The heavy sail moved suddenly and it hit Maria.

55:49.760 --> 55:53.840
She nearly fell into the sea, but she held onto the rail.

55:55.280 --> 55:56.720
They pulled the sail down.

55:58.000 --> 56:00.080
Well done, said Bob.

56:01.040 --> 56:04.320
Then he stood up slowly and leaned on Anna.

56:04.560 --> 56:07.760
Be careful, Bob, she said.

56:07.760 --> 56:11.840
I'm all right, Anna, he said.

56:13.120 --> 56:18.800
He looked at Tommy angrily, but I've never had pirates on my yacht,

56:19.520 --> 56:20.720
and I don't like it.

56:22.240 --> 56:24.240
Then Bob looked at Kit and said,

56:25.280 --> 56:26.960
you've been a stupid young man.

56:27.360 --> 56:28.960
Then Bob looked at the boat and said,

56:28.960 --> 56:30.080
you've been a stupid young man.

56:33.280 --> 56:35.280
Chapter eight, Moon Island.

56:37.120 --> 56:40.960
It was nearly daylight and the sky above the horizon was lighter now.

56:44.080 --> 56:48.400
From the deck of summer cloud, they could all see the big bay on Moon Island in front of them.

56:51.280 --> 56:52.720
There were already some fishing boats at sea.

56:53.040 --> 56:57.200
Two police officers waited at the harbor wall.

56:58.480 --> 57:02.080
They put Tommy into their car and came to talk to Bob.

57:04.080 --> 57:05.040
We know this man.

57:06.000 --> 57:09.360
He's Tommy Morito, said one of the officers.

57:10.480 --> 57:12.720
We've been looking for him for six months.

57:13.760 --> 57:15.360
He's robbed a lot of yachts.

57:16.640 --> 57:18.080
Some pirates live at sea.

57:18.880 --> 57:20.800
They sail after the big ships.

57:21.440 --> 57:23.440
But Tommy doesn't do that.

57:24.240 --> 57:28.400
He gets information about rich and famous clients on yachts.

57:29.520 --> 57:33.360
And he tricks stupid people like me, said Kit.

57:34.720 --> 57:41.040
Well, there are always two sides to every story, said the police officer.

57:42.000 --> 57:43.440
Why were you with him?

57:44.960 --> 57:49.760
His friend Jade asked me to get some information about Bob's clients,

57:50.400 --> 57:51.040
said Kit.

57:52.160 --> 57:53.680
It was for a new magazine.

57:54.800 --> 57:58.160
They promised to pay me and I said yes.

57:59.440 --> 58:00.960
Kit looked down at the ground.

58:02.080 --> 58:06.000
They wanted to rob the yacht, but I didn't know that.

58:07.200 --> 58:14.240
I didn't try to trick Anna, but I did give them information and I'm sorry about that.

58:14.320 --> 58:20.080
But you jumped onto Summer Cloud with the other pirates, didn't you?

58:20.960 --> 58:22.240
The police officer asked.

58:23.840 --> 58:29.920
Yes, but I'm not a pirate, Kit said quietly.

58:31.280 --> 58:32.880
I came to help Mr Chapman.

58:34.400 --> 58:36.400
He took his camera out of his jacket.

58:37.680 --> 58:39.680
I took photos of the pirates.

58:40.560 --> 58:47.040
I have photos of Tommy taking Miss Chilini's diamond rings and photos of Jade.

58:48.320 --> 58:50.960
That's good, said the police officer.

58:52.240 --> 58:53.920
Photos will help us a lot.

58:55.200 --> 58:58.240
Kit did help us, said Bob.

58:59.200 --> 59:01.120
He helped us get through the storm.

59:02.080 --> 59:03.520
He trusted those people.

59:04.400 --> 59:05.440
That was his problem.

59:07.120 --> 59:08.560
What happens now, officer?

59:10.000 --> 59:14.080
I've called the police on the mainland, said the police officer.

59:14.960 --> 59:19.360
They're going to send a helicopter to take Tommy Morito back today.

59:20.320 --> 59:23.360
The harbor police are already looking for Jade.

59:24.720 --> 59:27.680
We all need to ask you all some questions, too.

59:28.880 --> 59:30.880
We'll come back after your breakfast.

59:32.480 --> 59:36.560
The police officers got into the car and took Tommy away.

59:36.800 --> 59:45.120
Some people from the film crew came to take them to their hotel and gave them a big breakfast.

59:46.800 --> 59:49.840
Chaz took Kit to meet one of the film's cameramen.

59:51.680 --> 59:55.280
This young man wants to be a photographer, said Chaz.

59:56.480 --> 59:58.080
Can he work with you this week?

59:59.280 --> 01:00:00.320
He smiled at Kit.

01:00:01.520 --> 01:00:02.480
What do you think, Kit?

01:00:03.440 --> 01:00:05.360
You can learn a lot from the film crew.

01:00:06.560 --> 01:00:07.680
Why don't you stay with us?

01:00:09.040 --> 01:00:11.360
And maybe you can be in the film, too.

01:00:12.480 --> 01:00:13.200
Maria said,

01:00:14.160 --> 01:00:16.720
You'll earn some money to buy your new camera.

01:00:17.840 --> 01:00:19.440
Call your father and ask him.

01:00:21.040 --> 01:00:23.200
Kit looked at Maria and Chaz.

01:00:24.640 --> 01:00:27.040
Then he smiled for the first time that day.

01:00:28.960 --> 01:00:30.720
Thank you, he said.

01:00:32.240 --> 01:00:34.720
But it isn't a pirate film, is it?

01:00:37.360 --> 01:00:40.480
The sun shone and there was a good wind.

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:44.480
Anna stood at the rail of Summer Cloud.

01:00:46.000 --> 01:00:47.840
Moon Island was behind them.

01:00:48.960 --> 01:00:52.160
She could see Kit and Chaz and Maria on the harbour wall.

01:00:53.360 --> 01:00:53.840
Goodbye!

01:00:55.040 --> 01:00:55.600
Goodbye!

01:00:56.880 --> 01:00:59.280
We'll see you soon, she called.

01:01:00.800 --> 01:01:01.920
She sat down again.

01:01:03.840 --> 01:01:05.120
Is Bob angry with me?

01:01:06.080 --> 01:01:06.640
She thought.

01:01:07.920 --> 01:01:10.320
I told Kit about Bob's clients.

01:01:11.120 --> 01:01:13.440
And that was the start of all our problems.

01:01:15.600 --> 01:01:17.920
But Bob Chapman was a kind man.

01:01:20.240 --> 01:01:22.320
We all do stupid things, Anna.

01:01:23.120 --> 01:01:23.600
He said,

01:01:24.640 --> 01:01:25.920
Kit has learned that too.

01:01:27.200 --> 01:01:28.640
You did well yesterday.

01:01:29.920 --> 01:01:34.240
You helped to take down the mainsail and put it up again.

01:01:35.200 --> 01:01:37.840
You sailed Summer Cloud in a storm.

01:01:38.880 --> 01:01:40.240
That's not easy.

01:01:41.360 --> 01:01:43.600
Why don't you sail the yacht back?

01:01:44.560 --> 01:01:45.920
Anna smiled and said,

01:01:46.880 --> 01:01:47.600
Thanks Bob.

01:01:49.440 --> 01:01:52.080
They heard a noise in the sky and looked up.

01:01:53.120 --> 01:01:55.120
The police helicopter was above them.

01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:58.720
And inside it they could see Tommy Morito.

01:02:00.080 --> 01:02:01.440
Goodbye, pirate!

01:02:02.160 --> 01:02:03.120
Anna shouted.

01:02:04.080 --> 01:02:05.760
We won't see you again.

01:02:07.360 --> 01:02:09.120
Raised the mainsail, Anna.

01:02:09.920 --> 01:02:10.480
Said Bob.

01:02:11.920 --> 01:02:14.240
Anna pulled hard on the main rope.

01:02:15.040 --> 01:02:19.440
And soon the sail was higher in the air and full of wind.

01:02:21.040 --> 01:02:22.560
Soon they were out of the bay.

01:02:23.920 --> 01:02:24.640
She looked back,

01:02:25.520 --> 01:02:28.080
but she couldn't see the people on the harbour wall.

01:02:29.440 --> 01:02:32.080
But perhaps I'll see Kit again.

01:02:33.120 --> 01:02:35.120
She thought happily.

